ODM party leader Raila Odinga will make his showbiz debut today through a cameo in Emmanuel Musindi’s ‘Leo ni Leo remix’ video . According to the 38-second video trailer posted on social media on Tuesday, Raila is seen performing alongside the Luhya star in front of a troupe of backup dancers. Raila who is clad in a bomber jacket of Kenyan flag colours, is seen performing with the dancers as a lead singer. “Leo ni Leo (Today is Today)” My first ever music video drops online," Raila tweeted. "Set your reminders: My 1st ever song drops at 11am on the following link https://youtu.be/yf4eQDa2IgM and on my Facebook page as well. Tune in! #BabaTheArtist." The popular hit has been consistently featured in Raila’s campaign rallies. Raila who has been in India for the last one week is expected to return to Kenya when the song is released. His Azimio brigade has been traversing the country even as he prepares himself for the August elections.